title: US President Donald Trump speaks with Prime Minister Bill English
text:
US President Donald Trump speaks with Prime Minister Bill English Last updated 12:13, February 6 2017 CAMERON BURNELL/REUTERS 
Prime Minister Bill English thanked President Trump for support the US provided after the Kaikoura quake. 
Prime Minister Bill English has finally spoken with United States President Donald Trump, and thanked him. 
"The Prime Minister spoke with President Trump this morning," a spokesman said. "They discussed a number of issues including the growing New Zealand economy, along with the important trade, security and defence relationships between the two countries. The President and Prime Minister noted their respective positions on the recent US Executive Order on immigration on that country. "Prime Minister English thanked the President for the US support during the Kaikoura earthquake." 
- More soon
